_meanings:
{@--3@} (As a separable preposition with
<ab>abl.</ab>) it shows either ({%a%}) the limit
inceptive ({#aBiviDi#}), from, ever since,
away from, out of, off, from among;
{#AmUlAt SrotumicCAmi#} <ls>Ś. 1</ls>; {#bahuBya#}
{#A#} from out of many; {#A janmanaH#}
<ls>Ś. 5. 25</ls> ever since (her) birth;
{#A manoH#} <ls>U. 6. 18.</ls> ({%b%}) Or, it 
expresses the limit exclusive or 
conclusive ({#maryAdA#}), till, until, upto, as
far as, unto; {#AN maryAdABiviDyoH#}  
<ls>P. II. 1. 13</ls>; see {#aBiviDi#}; {#A#} 
{#paritozAdviduzAM#} <ls>Ś. 1. 2</ls> till the learned are 
satisfied; {#A kElAsAt#} <ls>Me. 11</ls> upto or as
far as Kailāsa; {#odakAMtAt#} <ls>Ś. 4</ls>;  
<ls>U. 1. 37</ls>; <ls>V. 2. 2.</ls> In this sense {#A#} 
sometimes governs the <ab>acc.</ab>; {#SatamA jAtIH#}
upto a hundred births. ({%c%}) In both
these senses {#A#} frequently enters 

into compound, forming either 
Avyayībhāva <ab>comp.</ab> or compound 
adjectives; {#AbAlaM#} (or {#A bAleByaH#}) {#hariBaktiH#}
commencing with or including 
children; {#Amukti#} (or {#AmukteH#}) {#saMsAraH#} <ls>Sk.</ls>
till final emancipation; {#AmeKalaM#}  
<ls>Ku. 1. 5</ls> as far as.; {#AmaraRaM#} <ls>Pt. 1</ls> till
death; {#AgopAlaM nanftuH#} <ls>K. 70</ls> down to
the cowherd; {#AgopAlA dvijAtayaH#}
including the cowherds. Sometimes
the compound so formed stands
as the first member of other 
compounds, {#so'#} 
{#hamAjanmaSudDAnAmAPalodayakarmaRAM .#} 
{#AsamudrakzitISAnAmAnAkaraTavartmanAM#} <ls>R. 1. 5</ls>; {#AgaMqavilaMbi#} <ls>Ś. 6. 17</ls>;
{#AkarRalaMbi#} <ls>M. 5. 10.</ls> ({%d%}) Used
with <ab>loc.</ab> it has the sense of ‘in’,
‘at’ (mostly <ab>Ved.</ab>); {#gAvo na yavasezvA#}
<ls>Rv. 1. 91. 13.</ls>
